    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Summarize long emails with Google Drive and Microsoft Teams on autopilot\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nSummarize long emails with Google Drive and Microsoft Teams on autopilot. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual summarization is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Read Recent from Google Sheets → Newest First → Trim to Digest Size → Summarize Content (AI) → Render as HTML → Post Digest to Microsoft Teams → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating summarization in legal\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Improves response time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "19c85319-32ac-61b4-ba65-631c6dbfe293",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "ac4e8205-c84e-0266-6840-fd28f842f124",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "a62453f6-2fd3-7823-be06-9392d694f166",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "87450038-1fbc-3adc-fa0f-6387f560e2ec",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your summarization process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
